HEADWORD: Plasm
<hw>Plasm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>plasma</ets>
anything formed or molded, that which is molded, Gr. <?/, <?/, from <?/
to form, mold: cf. F. <ets>plasme</ets>. Cf. <er>Plasma</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A mold or matrix in which anything is cast or formed to
a particular shape.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

